# TCP/IP Model – Hands-on Learning

This repository contains hands-on networking labs focused on TCP/IP model,
packet analysis, and real-world network behavior.

Goal: Understand how data moves across networks using practical tools like Wireshark and Linux commands.

---

# Tools Used

- Wireshark
- Cisco Packet Tracer
- Linux terminal (Ubuntu)
- TCPDump

---

# What I Can Explain After This Section

- How a website is actually loaded step-by-step
- What happens inside a TCP connection
- How DNS translates domains to IPs
- Why HTTPS is secure at packet level
- How data moves across network layers

---

# Next Steps

- Deep dive into DNS + HTTP flow analysis
- Build more Wireshark capture labs
- Start subnetting + routing layer integration
